This repository composes, but does not vendor, third-party software. The built
image contains:

  - IIC-OSIC-TOOLS (docker.io/hpretl/iic-osic-tools) and the EDA tools + open
    PDKs it bundles. The IIC-OSIC-TOOLS recipe is Apache-2.0; each bundled tool
    and PDK is distributed under its own license and retained unchanged.

  - The Vyges layer, installed at build time from public vyges-tools/* releases:
      * vyges-loom (design-data foundation) — Apache-2.0.
      * the vyges CLI — closed-source, distributed as a binary only.
      * per-foundry calibration data and plugins, where applicable, are
        distributed separately under their own terms and are not part of this
        repository.

The OSS sign-off path (KLayout / magic / netgen / ngspice + PDKs) is complete and
self-sufficient, and never depends on a non-open Vyges component — even though the
Vyges CLI is on the default PATH in this Vyges container.

Each build's exact upstream image digest and Vyges component versions/licenses
are recorded in the image's manifest.json.
